oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cleaning out the water crossing
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Mr. Susong (on the left) and Joseph Jonas Myers (1883-1945) (on the right) are pictured cleaning out the ford between the store and the depot on the Little River. The covered railroad bridge can be seen in the background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Men; Rivers; Covered bridges
